data.description: Large south-facing balcony with DROP DEAD GORGEOUS VIEW FOR LIFE!  Stunning views from this south-facing balcony overlooking Lake Michigan, Monroe Harbor, Grant/Millennium and Maggie Daley Parks, and the iconic Chicago Skyline!     Outer Drive East is a full-amenity luxury condo building with a 10,000 sq. ft. state-of-the-art fitness and recreational spa. The 400 Fitness and Spa offers a sunny indoor swimming pool, basketball, racquetball, free weights, machine weights, many various cardio equipment, a library, massage therapy, a child's playroom, and a new function room with a 100" screen and open kitchen and adjacent Zoom compatible conference room. Outdoor amenities include extensive sun decks and communal grills. The Outer Drive East building has a package delivery to unit option, three-car wash stalls, and three bike rooms. The building has social groups and activities. Monthly assessments include heat, a/c, gas, cable, internet, health club, and pool.    Outer Drive East is situated in the vibrant New Eastside neighborhood with restaurants, parks, grocery stores, and much more. Easy walking distance to Michigan Avenue and the Loop (central business district). Easy access to public transportation and expressways. Chicago's "New Eastside" neighborhood is an oasis amidst the hustle and bustle of the downtown Chicago Loop. Cul-de-sac neighborhood with minimal through traffic. Monthly assessments include heat, a/c, gas, cable, and health club. Assigned parking is available for 220/mo per car. The building, Outer Drive East, is almost new again. So many renovations and great building finances. New windows, new 5-star resort-like health-fitness - spa, racquetball, basketball, free weights, machine weights, cardio, massage therapy, child's playroom, famous geodesic domed year-round sunny pool. Hospitality/party room, business center with resident computers and a printer, library, community BBQ grills and a bi-level sun deck. HOA includes heat, a/c, gas, cable, cable with TiVo 6 DVR, 24/7 lobby desk, security and door attendants. 3 bike rooms and 3 car washing stalls. Restaurant bar/grill, beauty and nail salon and several other businesses are located on the 7th floor. Very friendly building with lots of social activities and events such as a book club, world affairs club, bingo, summer picnic, children's Halloween party, children's holiday party, and a resident holiday party, to name a few. Great Outer Drive East community in the vibrant New Eastside neighborhood. Come see the exciting "New Eastside" neighborhood. There are two fine grocery options, including Bockwinkel's Harbor Market (across the street) or a huge Mariano's grocery store with many item options for your daily shopping needs. Nestled in the New Eastside neighborhood is Lakeshore East Park. This oasis in the neighborhood's nucleus includes large grassy areas, a children's playlot, and a dog park. 30-minute free parking for showings, guests, and deliveries. The New Eastside neighborhood is bordered by the lakefront, the Chicago River, Michigan Ave, and Grant Park. The Chicago Riverwalk is alive with activities for all ages. Maggie Daley Park to the south has an enormous "dreamlike fantasy" play area, climbing walls, mini-golf, Park District activities including day camps, tennis courts, and the "Ribbon Ice Skating Rink". Easy to show. 30 Min free parking in the building.
